---
interface Props {
  city: string;
  region: string;
  neighborhoods?: string[];
}

const { city, region, neighborhoods } = Astro.props;

// Build the opening line based on whether neighborhoods are provided
const openingLine = neighborhoods && neighborhoods.length > 0
  ? `Whether you're in ${neighborhoods.join(', ')}, or serving the broader ${region} area, the problem is the same: you do great work, your customers are happy, but contractors who need you can't find you online. You're buried on page 2 or 3 of Google while competitors with worse reviews get the calls.`
  : `Whether you're serving ${city} or the broader ${region} area, the problem is the same: you do great work, your customers are happy, but contractors who need you can't find you online. You're buried on page 2 or 3 of Google while competitors with worse reviews get the calls.`;
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-24 section-checkers">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
      Why {city} Contractors Struggle to Get Consistent Leads
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      {openingLine}
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      You rely on word-of-mouth and referrals. Some months are great. Some months are slow. You can't control the lead flow, which means you can't control growth. You've probably tried marketing beforeâ€”maybe an agency that didn't deliver, maybe DIY that took too much time. Either way, you're still here looking for something that actually works.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8">
      Here's the truth: most contractors in {city} have the same problem. It's not unique to your business. You're not doing anything wrong. The marketing agencies selling you services just aren't building complete systems that actually generate consistent revenue.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
